---- MODULE VoucherCancel ----
------------------------------- INSTANCE FiniteSets ---------- --*) This instance declares that the set of natural numbers is a finite *)  NATURAL Set                               |)    THEOREM NatIsFin SET_THEORY            (|--* Infinite sets are not allowed in TLA+           FORALL i IN {1 .. }   [NOT] IS FINITE NaturalNumbers ] ) -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA ZIndicesIsFinite --* Finite sets are finite *- SET_THEORY    FORALL s IN Vouchers   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAINs(Zindicess)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA ZSeqOfLengthIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL S IN Vouchers   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAN(Zseqoflength)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA ZSeqIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL S IN Vouchers   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAN(Zseq)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA ZLenIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL s IN Vouchers   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAN(Zlen)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA RotationIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL s IN Vouchers   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAN(Rotatin)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA RotationsIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL s IN Vouchers   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAN(Rotatin)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA HStateIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL h IN Holders   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAN(Hstate)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA IStateIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL i IN Issuers   [ NOT] IS FINITE (DOMAN(Istate)) ]                        -*) The type of the expression DOMAIN is a set, so we cannot take its domain. Instead *)  LEMMA VTPStateIsFinite --* Finte sets are finite *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i \in Issuers } : (DOMAN(Hstate)) = TRUE, DOMAIN IS FINITE ) -*) The type of the expression  *- SET_THEORY FORALL vtp IN [VoucherTran]   sACTIONS {Prepared(vh[i], vlc) | i